Section 1:
Act 806 of the Regular Session
1 State of Arkansas As Engrossed: H3/20/25
A Bill
2 95th General Assembly
3 Regular Session, 2025 HOUSE BILL 1833
4
5 By: Representatives M. Shepherd, Achor, F. Allen, Brooks, M. Brown, Cavenaugh, Clowney, A. Collins,
6 Eaves, Evans, Gramlich, Hawk, L. Johnson, Maddox, Perry, Pilkington, Torres, Tosh, Underwood,
7 Warren
8 By: Senators B. Davis, J. Boyd, Hester, G. Leding
9
For An Act To Be Entitled
10
11 AN ACT TO AMEND THE LAW CONCERNING HIGHER EDUCATION;
12 TO AMEND THE LAW CONCERNING THE ADMISSIONS AT THE
13 UNIVERSITY OF ARKANSAS COLLEGE OF MEDICINE; AND FOR
14 OTHER PURPOSES.
15
16
Subtitle
17
18 TO AMEND THE LAW CONCERNING THE
19 ADMISSIONS AT THE UNIVERSITY OF ARKANSAS
20 COLLEGE OF MEDICINE.
21
22 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
23
24 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code § 6-64-406(b), concerning the allocation of
25 enrollment positions at the University of Arkansas College of Medicine for
26 the freshman medical class among congressional districts, is amended to read
27 as follows:
28 (b)(1)(A) The board shall allocate the first seventy percent (70%) of
29 the first one hundred fifty (150) enrollment positions for the freshman
30 medical class among Arkansas congressional districts, using the population of
31 each congressional district as determined by the last federal decennial
32 census to determine that district's proportion of the freshman positions so
33 allocated and shall assign those apportioned enrollment positions for each
34 district to those applicants who are legal residents in that particular
35 congressional district twenty-five (25) positions to each congressional
36 district.
*CRH230*
03-20-2025 09:50:41 CRH230
As Engrossed: H3/20/25 HB1833
1 (B) The board shall give additional consideration to rural
2 applicants from medically underserved areas in an effort to address health
3 disparities If there are not twenty-five (25) applicants from a congressional
4 district who meet published admissions standards and accept an offer of
5 acceptance, the remaining positions for that congressional district first
6 shall be filled by qualified applicants who are Arkansas residents and then
7 by applicants that are most likely to complete the program and reside in
8 Arkansas.
9 (2)(A) The next fifteen percent (15%) of the first one hundred
10 fifty (150) freshman enrollment positions shall be allocated to the state at
11 large and assigned to applicants who are legal residents of any place within
12 Arkansas An additional twenty-five (25) positions shall be allocated to
13 applicants who are Arkansas residents.
14 (B) However, in allocating the fifteen percent (15%) to
15 the state at large, the board may allocate not to exceed one-third (⅓) of the
16 fifteen percent (15%) of the first one hundred fifty (150) freshman
17 enrollment positions to applicants who do not actually reside in the state
18 but who were born and reared and attended public schools in Arkansas and who
19 in addition thereto shall meet two (2) or more of the following criteria:
20 (i) Applicant is a registered voter in Arkansas;
21 (ii) Applicant holds a current valid Arkansas
22 driver's license;
23 (iii) Applicant or parents of applicant are Arkansas
24 taxpayers;
25 (iv) Parent of applicant resides in or is employed
26 in Arkansas; and
27 (v) Applicant meets other related criteria as may be
28 prescribed by the board If there are not twenty-five (25) applicants who are
29 Arkansas residents who meet published admissions standards and accept an
30 offer of acceptance, then the remaining positions first shall be filled by
31 qualified applicants who have ties to Arkansas and then by applicants who are
32 most likely to complete the program and reside in Arkansas.
33 (3) The remaining fifteen percent (15%) of the first one hundred
34 fifty (150) freshman enrollment positions may be assigned either to legal
35 residents or to nonresidents, however, any qualified legal resident shall
36 have a preference in securing an assignment to a position when compared to a
2 03-20-2025 09:50:41 CRH230
As Engrossed: H3/20/25 HB1833
1 nonresident, and the total number of nonresidents assigned positions shall
2 not exceed fifteen percent (15%) of the first one hundred fifty (150)
3 freshman enrollment positions assigned for any school year Positions in
4 excess of the positions provided under subdivisions (b)(1) and (2) of this
5 section may be filled by applicants at large.
6 (4) The board may provide for an alteration in the percentages
7 set forth in this subsection only if the adherence to these percentages would
8 endanger the accredited rating of the University of Arkansas College of
9 Medicine as determined by the standards of the Association of American
10 Medical Colleges.
11
12 /s/M. Shepherd
